p Casey's site was one of the few times I created a separate code base for the mobile styles and some of the markup. This was a decision I made halfway into writing CSS responsive rules because there was still a lot of behavior going on that I felt should only be present on the desktop.
p Specifically, I wanted users on the Desktop to enjoy the benefits of parallax scrolling, while users on mobile may need to access information like pricing and contact details more quickly.
